Oregano was sold as a common seasoning through ''[[Aurora's Whole Realms Catalogue]]'', priced at two [[silver]] [[coin|pieces]] per ounce.

Oregano was grown in the lush [[herb]] gardens of the [[Sarahin]] fortress in the Haunted Lands of Zakhara. The aromas of [[mint]], [[sage (herb)|sage]], [[rosemary]], [[dill]], [[parsley]], [[cilantro]], [[thyme]], and oregano all clashed with each other and these were ready to be used in the fortress's nearby kitchens.

In the jungles of the [[Malatran Plateau]] in [[Kara-Tur]] oregano grew near [[Koshiva]]n and [[Rudra]]n settlements.{{Cite organized play/LJ/Recipe for Disaster|7}} The herb was also a known food consumed by the [[Nubari (ancient)|Ancient Nubari]]. One of the ancient recipes using oregano was discovered and turned into the [[Zucchini Saiyama style]] dish.{{Cite organized play/LJ/Recipe for Disaster|22}}
